    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/10–951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States</hi> (<gloss target="#t_GATT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">GATT</hi>
                    </gloss>) <hi rend="italic">Delegation to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-09T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 9, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tagg1">Tagg</gloss> 71. Re Belg dollar import restrictions.
                    Suetens advised US del Oct 8 that Belg has dropped intention use Art XIV <gloss
                        target="#t_IMF1">IMF</gloss> and now favors Art XII <gloss target="#t_GATT1"
                        >GATT</gloss> as most appropriate. However indicated Art XXV <gloss
                        target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> still attractive and wld be willing accept
                    outcome ⅔ vote. Canads have made strong representations to Belg del for immed
                    removal restrictions. Suetens leaving for Brussels Thurs to return Geneva fol
                    Tues. Indicated he personally favored withdrawal restrictions and wld urge that
                    course on govt. Matter will not be raised now in <gloss target="#t_CP1"
                        >CP</gloss>s at least until Suetens return Oct 16 or 17. Meanwhile Suetens
                    advises (Oct 9) that Saad favoring use Art XIV. Will discuss this with Saad
                    promptly.</p>
                <p>Dept also pass Ottawa, sent Dept <gloss target="#t_Tagg1">Tagg</gloss> 71, rptd
                    info Paris 87 for <gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss>, Brussels 12, Ottawa
                    1.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
